{
  "texts": [
    "This disparity underscores the need for innovative teaching methodologies that can enrich the learning experience and enhance comprehension in mechanical engineering education.In the rapidly evolving landscape of Natural Language Processing (NLP), the emergence of Large Language Models (LLMs) signifies a transformative paradigm shift in artificial intelligence capabilities [12].",
    "NLP, dedicated to facilitating computerhuman language interaction, encompasses various applications ranging from language translation, content summarization to sentiment analysis [13].",
    "Conventional NLPs are constrained in offering tailored solutions for specific applications through supervised training [14].",
    "In this paradigm, models undergo fine-tuning on labeled training data, and often require further pre-training on domain-specific datasets to achieve optimal performance.",
    "In contrast, LLMs, characterized by their expansive size and exceptional few-shot learning capabilities, transcend these limitations by introducing the in-context learning approach [15][16][17]."
  ]
}